def load_time_series_data(filepath, time_column, y_column, delimiter=',', date_format=None, resample_freq=None):
    print(f"Loading: {filepath}")
    try:
        df = pd.read_csv(filepath, sep=delimiter, engine='python')
        df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()
            
        df[time_column] = pd.to_datetime(df[time_column], format=date_format)
        df = df.set_index(time_column).sort_index()
        
        plot_data = df[[y_column]].copy() 

        plot_data[y_column] = pd.to_numeric(plot_data[y_column], errors='coerce')

        missing_count = plot_data[y_column].isnull().sum()
        if missing_count > 0:
            print(f"Found {missing_count} missing value(s).")
            print("Filling gaps using linear interpolation...")
            plot_data[y_column] = plot_data[y_column].interpolate(method='linear')

        if resample_freq:
            plot_data = plot_data.resample(resample_freq).mean()
            print(f"Resampled to {resample_freq} frequency.")
        
        print(f"Successfully loaded and processed {filepath}.\n")
        return plot_data

    except FileNotFoundError:
        print(f"File not found: {filepath}\n")
        return Noneths
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"An error occurred during loading: {e}\n")
        return None

def time_plots(df, y_column, title):
    with plt.style.context('grayscale'):
        plt.figure(figsize=(15,6))
        df[y_column].plot()
        
        plt.title(title,fontsize=16)
        plt.xlabel("Time")
        plt.ylabel(y_column)
        plt.grid(True, which='both', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
        plt.show()

def analyze_and_transform(filepath, time_column, y_column, transformation, delimiter=',',date_format=None, resample_freq=None, end_date=None):
    df = load_time_series_data(
        filepath=filepath,
        time_column=time_column,
        y_column=y_column,
        delimiter=delimiter,
        date_format=date_format,
        resample_freq=resample_freq
    )
    if df is None:
        print("There occured an error with loading the file.\n")
        return

    if end_date:
        try:
            df = df.loc[df.index <= end_date]
            print(f"Successfully sliced data to end at {end_date}.\n")
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Error during slicing: {e}\n")
            return

    time_plots(df,y_column, f"Initial plot: {y_column}")

    if transformation == 'none':
        print("No transformation is needed")
        return df
        
    print(f"Applying {transformation} transformation")
    transformed_df = df.copy()

    try:
        if transformation == "log":
            transformed_df[y_column] = np.log(transformed_df[y_column])
            plot_title = f"Log-transformed {y_column}"

        elif transformation == "boxcox":
            transformed_data, optimal_lambda = stats.boxcox(transformed_df[y_column])
            transformed_df[y_column] = transformed_data
            print(f"Box-Cox transformation complete. Optimal lambda () = {optimal_lambda:.4f}")
            plot_title = f"Box-Cox transformed ( = {optimal_lambda:.2f}): {y_column}"
        else:
            print(f"Error: unknown transformation '{transformation}'. Please use 'none', 'log', or 'boxcox'.\n")
            return
        time_plots(transformed_df, y_column, plot_title)
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"An error occurred during transformation: {e}\n")
    return transformed_df

def plot_stl_decomposition(df, y_column, title, period):
    if df is None:
        print(f"Cannot perform STL on '{title}': DataFrame is None.\n")
        return
    
    try:
        series_to_decompose = df[y_column].dropna()
        
        if len(series_to_decompose) < 2 * period:
            print(f"Error: Not enough data for STL. Need at least 2 full periods ({2*period} obs), but have {len(series_to_decompose)}.")
            return

        stl = STL(series_to_decompose, period=period)
        result = stl.fit()
        
        fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3, ax4) = plt.subplots(4, 1, figsize=(12, 12), sharex=True)
        
        ax1.plot(result.observed)
        ax1.set_ylabel('Observed')
        
        ax2.plot(result.trend)
        ax2.set_ylabel('Trend')
        
        ax3.plot(result.seasonal)
        ax3.set_ylabel('Seasonal')
        
        ax4.plot(result.resid)
        ax4.set_ylabel('Remainder')
        
        ax4.set_xlabel('Time')
        fig.suptitle(title, y=1.02, fontsize=16)
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

        seasonal_adjusted_df = pd.DataFrame(result.observed - result.seasonal)
        seasonal_adjusted_df.columns = [y_column]
        print(f"Created seasonally adjusted series for {title}.")
        
        return seasonal_adjusted_df 

    except Exception as e:
        print(f"An error occurred during STL decomposition: {e}\n")
